				\begin{document}$${\mathrm{\Delta }}\phi _{41} = \frac{{2\pi }}{N}$$\end{document}. The 1 × L × M × N = 1 × 3 × 3 × 3 phase-cycling scheme selected here retrieves, among others, the rephasing (α = −1, β = 1, γ = 1, δ = −1) and nonrephasing (α = 1, β = −1, γ = 1, δ = −1) signals for which each visible pulse interacts once with the sample.
